article.headline: Evansville 64, Wichita St. 56
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Shy Ely scored 18 points, including a key 3-pointer in the second half, as Evansville surged to a 64-56 victory over Wichita State in the Missouri Valley Conference on Wednesday night. The Purple Aces (7-15, 2-10 MVC) trailed 31-20 at the break, but went on a 24-13 run capped by a Jason Holsinger 3-pointer to tie the score at 44-44 with 9:28 left. Evansville took a 4-point lead on free throws before Ely nailed a 3-pointer to stretch the lead to seven. A pair of layups by Nate Garner and a 3-pointer by Holsinger made the margin 14, and the Shockers got no closer than six the rest of the way. Holsinger finished with 14 points and four assists. Phillip Thomasson had 10 points for the Shockers (9-14, 2-10), who outrebounded Evansville 36-31 and outscored the Purple Aces in the paint 16-12. The Aces were 26-of-32 from the free-throw line, while Wichita State went 16-of-24. Evansville scored 17 points off turnovers.
